{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0126DyKVU9yNPjCPH6VXViD6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Autonomous Dev Progress Log\n     2→\n     3→Each entry is appended by the autonomous agent after completing work.\n     4→\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→## 2026-03-18 — Run 1\n     8→\n     9→### What was done\n    10→\n    11→**1. valueSortify — Critical security fix (PR #9, merged)**\n    12→- Upgraded jspdf from v2.5.2 to v4.2.1 and jspdf-autotable from v3.8.4 to v5.0.7\n    13→- Fixed 3 vulnerabilities: prototype pollution (critical), ReDoS bypass (high), XSS via dompurify (moderate)\n    14→- Updated `ResultsPhase.jsx` to use the new `applyPlugin()` API required by jspdf-autotable v5\n    15→- Build verified, 0 vulnerabilities remaining\n    16→\n    17→**2. groceryGenius — npm audit fix (PR #34, merged)**\n    18→- Applied `npm audit fix` to resolve 8 of 16 security findings (non-breaking updates)\n    19→- Fixed: undici HTTP smuggling (high), glob command injection (high), minimatch ReDoS (high), rollup path traversal (high), qs DoS, lodash prototype pollution, on-headers manipulation, brace-expansion ReDoS\n    20→- Remaining 8 moderate esbuild findings are dev-only transitive deps via drizzle-kit\n    21→\n    22→**3. job-scraper — Unit test suite (PR #8, merged)**\n    23→- Added 59 unit tests using Node's built-in `node:test` runner (zero new dependencies)\n    24→- Covers all 3 ATS adapters: Greenhouse, Ashby, Lever (URL parsing, salary extraction, requirements extraction)\n    25→- Tests base adapter infrastructure: DomainRateLimiter, error classes, Zod schema validation\n    26→- Exported previously-private pure helper functions to enable direct testing\n    27→- Added `npm test` script to package.json\n    28→\n    29→### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n    30→- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n    31→- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n    32→- **waymo-sim**: Bug in `entity.py` line 123 — hardcoded `0.1` divisor in waypoint interpolation P-controller instead of actual `dt`. `world.py reset()` doesn't restore entity positions.\n    33→- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug.\n    34→- **runCoach**: Empty repo — only README and LICENSE.\n    35→\n    36→---\n    37→\n    38→## 2026-03-18 — Run 2\n    39→\n    40→### What was done\n    41→\n    42→**waymo-sim — Two engine bug fixes (PR #8, merged)**\n    43→- Fixed hardcoded `0.1` divisor in `entity.py:interpolate_waypoint()` P-controller. The acceleration calculation now uses the actual `dt` parameter passed from the world engine, so NPC vehicles follow waypoints correctly at any timestep size.\n    44→- Fixed `world.py:reset()` to restore entity positions, headings, and speeds to their initial values. Previously it only cleared collision flags, leaving entities at their last simulated positions.\n    45→- Added 2 regression tests covering both bugs (28/28 tests pass).\n    46→\n    47→### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n    48→- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n    49→- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n    50→- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug.\n    51→- **runCoach**: Empty repo — only README and LICENSE.\n    52→- **waymo-sim**: `test_env.py` can't run due to missing `gymnasium` dependency (not in requirements.txt). Pre-existing issue.\n    53→\n    54→---\n    55→\n    56→## 2026-03-18 — Run 3\n    57→\n    58→### What was done\n    59→\n    60→**1. activity-tracker — Two bug fixes + first test suite (PR #1, merged)**\n    61→- Fixed greedy `.*` → `.*?` in `redactCommand` curl bearer regex (`shell-history.js:90`). Previously over-redacted non-sensitive headers in multi-header curl commands.\n    62→- Fixed shallow copy bug in `loadConfig` fallback (`config.js:49`). `{ ...DEFAULTS }` was replaced with `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(DEFAULTS))` to prevent config mutations from corrupting the shared DEFAULTS object.\n    63→- Added 7 regression tests using `node:test` (zero dependencies) covering both bugs.\n    64→- Added `npm test` script to package.json.\n    65→\n    66→**2. pezantTools — High-severity fast-xml-parser fix (PR #25, merged)**\n    67→- Ran `npm audit fix` to patch fast-xml-parser entity expansion bypass (GHSA-8gc5-j5rx-235r, high severity).\n    68→- Reduced vulnerabilities from 6 (1 high, 5 low) to 5 (all low).\n    69→- Remaining 5 low-severity findings are transitive deps of `@google-cloud/storage` requiring a breaking major version downgrade — not worth the risk.\n    70→\n    71→### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n    72→- **pezantTools**: 5 low vulnerabilities remaining (transitive @google-cloud/storage deps). Open PR #23 for zip-slip security still pending review.\n    73→- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n    74→- **waymo-sim**: `test_env.py` can't run due to missing `gymnasium` dependency (not in requirements.txt). Pre-existing issue.\n    75→- **runCoach**: Empty repo — only README and LICENSE.\n    76→\n    77→---\n    78→\n    79→## 2026-03-18 — Run 4\n    80→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fd6ea26a-cb05-47a5-8060-bb9857e501ca","uuid":"09f1c177-c9c4-4ff2-9986-3f86fd2a724c","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:30:49.733Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"REDACTED_REPOS_ROOT/autonomousDev/logs/progress.md","content":"# Autonomous Dev Progress Log\n\nEach entry is appended by the autonomous agent after completing work.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-18 — Run 1\n\n### What was done\n\n**1. valueSortify — Critical security fix (PR #9, merged)**\n- Upgraded jspdf from v2.5.2 to v4.2.1 and jspdf-autotable from v3.8.4 to v5.0.7\n- Fixed 3 vulnerabilities: prototype pollution (critical), ReDoS bypass (high), XSS via dompurify (moderate)\n- Updated `ResultsPhase.jsx` to use the new `applyPlugin()` API required by jspdf-autotable v5\n- Build verified, 0 vulnerabilities remaining\n\n**2. groceryGenius — npm audit fix (PR #34, merged)**\n- Applied `npm audit fix` to resolve 8 of 16 security findings (non-breaking updates)\n- Fixed: undici HTTP smuggling (high), glob command injection (high), minimatch ReDoS (high), rollup path traversal (high), qs DoS, lodash prototype pollution, on-headers manipulation, brace-expansion ReDoS\n- Remaining 8 moderate esbuild findings are dev-only transitive deps via drizzle-kit\n\n**3. job-scraper — Unit test suite (PR #8, merged)**\n- Added 59 unit tests using Node's built-in `node:test` runner (zero new dependencies)\n- Covers all 3 ATS adapters: Greenhouse, Ashby, Lever (URL parsing, salary extraction, requirements extraction)\n- Tests base adapter infrastructure: DomainRateLimiter, error classes, Zod schema validation\n- Exported previously-private pure helper functions to enable direct testing\n- Added `npm test` script to package.json\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n- **waymo-sim**: Bug in `entity.py` line 123 — hardcoded `0.1` divisor in waypoint interpolation P-controller instead of actual `dt`. `world.py reset()` doesn't restore entity positions.\n- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug.\n- **runCoach**: Empty repo — only README and LICENSE.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-18 — Run 2\n\n### What was done\n\n**waymo-sim — Two engine bug fixes (PR #8, merged)**\n- Fixed hardcoded `0.1` divisor in `entity.py:interpolate_waypoint()` P-controller. The acceleration calculation now uses the actual `dt` parameter passed from the world engine, so NPC vehicles follow waypoints correctly at any timestep size.\n- Fixed `world.py:reset()` to restore entity positions, headings, and speeds to their initial values. Previously it only cleared collision flags, leaving entities at their last simulated positions.\n- Added 2 regression tests covering both bugs (28/28 tests pass).\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: 6 vulnerabilities (1 high fast-xml-parser). Has open PR #23 for zip-slip security.\n- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n- **activity-tracker**: Shell history `redactCommand` regex has greedy `.*` issue; config shallow copy bug.\n- **runCoach**: Empty repo — only README and LICENSE.\n- **waymo-sim**: `test_env.py` can't run due to missing `gymnasium` dependency (not in requirements.txt). Pre-existing issue.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-18 — Run 3\n\n### What was done\n\n**1. activity-tracker — Two bug fixes + first test suite (PR #1, merged)**\n- Fixed greedy `.*` → `.*?` in `redactCommand` curl bearer regex (`shell-history.js:90`). Previously over-redacted non-sensitive headers in multi-header curl commands.\n- Fixed shallow copy bug in `loadConfig` fallback (`config.js:49`). `{ ...DEFAULTS }` was replaced with `JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(DEFAULTS))` to prevent config mutations from corrupting the shared DEFAULTS object.\n- Added 7 regression tests using `node:test` (zero dependencies) covering both bugs.\n- Added `npm test` script to package.json.\n\n**2. pezantTools — High-severity fast-xml-parser fix (PR #25, merged)**\n- Ran `npm audit fix` to patch fast-xml-parser entity expansion bypass (GHSA-8gc5-j5rx-235r, high severity).\n- Reduced vulnerabilities from 6 (1 high, 5 low) to 5 (all low).\n- Remaining 5 low-severity findings are transitive deps of `@google-cloud/storage` requiring a breaking major version downgrade — not worth the risk.\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: 5 low vulnerabilities remaining (transitive @google-cloud/storage deps). Open PR #23 for zip-slip security still pending review.\n- **promptlibrary**: 1 moderate Next.js vulnerability. Has open PRs #8, #9.\n- **waymo-sim**: `test_env.py` can't run due to missing `gymnasium` dependency (not in requirements.txt). Pre-existing issue.\n- **runCoach**: Empty repo — only README and LICENSE.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-18 — Run 4\n","numLines":80,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1055}}}
