mpermonkey-duplicate-button-TVdw9)\n- llm-context: deleted 1 remote branch (claude/initial-setup)\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade (CSS-first config migration, substantial effort)\n- **trustedCircle**: All Tier 1 features complete. Next work would be Tier 2: trust badges, review reactions, responsive mobile, image support\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 29\n\n### What was done\n\n**trustedCircle — Review reactions (Tier 2 #6) (PR #26, auto-merged)**\n- New `reactions` table with `(review_id, user_id, type)` unique constraint and indexes on review_id and user_id\n- Two reaction types: \"Helpful\" (thumbs up) and \"Agree\" (heart)\n- `POST /api/reviews/:id/react` — toggles a reaction (add if not exists, remove if exists), returns `{toggled, type}`\n- `GET /api/reviews/:id/reactions?userId=` — returns counts per type and current user's active reactions\n- `ReactionButtons` component with optimistic UI updates and error rollback\n- Reaction buttons appear on all ReviewCard instances (homepage, category, person, search, circle pages) and ReviewDetailPage\n- Larger \"Helpful\" / \"Agree\" labels shown on detail page, compact icon-only on cards\n- Design system styling: moss green for helpful, ember for agree, pill-shaped buttons with border\n- Uses existing `useUserId` hook for anonymous user identity (localStorage UUID)\n- Zod validation schema (`toggleReactionSchema`) for type safety\n- 14 new tests covering toggle on/off, both types on same review, 404 for unknown review, invalid type, missing userId, user isolation, reaction counts, empty state, anonymous counts, user-scoped reactions\n- 69 total tests (was 55), all passing\n- TypeScript type check clean, build verified, API endpoints verified via curl\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: 