3-20 — Run 37\n   900→\n   901→### What was done\n   902→\n   903→**trustedCircle — Share links (Tier 3 #12) (PR #41, auto-merged)**\n   904→- `ShareButton` component with clipboard copy + Web Share API (native share sheet on mobile), pill-shaped design with \"Copied!\" feedback\n   905→- Share button added to 4 pages: ReviewDetailPage, PersonPage, CategoryPage, ComparePage\n   906→- Server-side OG meta tags middleware (`og-tags.ts`):\n   907→  - Detects social media bot user-agents (Facebook, Twitter, Discord, Slack, LinkedIn, Telegram, WhatsApp, Google, Bing)\n   908→  - Serves dynamic `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:image`, `og:url`, and Twitter Card meta tags\n   909→  - Supports 4 entity types: reviews, reviewer profiles, categories, comparisons\n   910→  - Handles base path stripping for production deployment\n   911→  - Fallback default OG tags for unknown/home paths\n   912→- 12 new tests: 8 for `getOgMeta` (all entity types, unknown entities, base path stripping, unmatched paths) + 4 for `renderOgHtml` (tag rendering, image inclusion/omission, HTML entity escaping)\n   913→- 136 total tests (was 124), all passing, TypeScript clean, build verified\n   914→\n   915→### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n   916→- **trustedCircle**: All Tier 3 features now complete (#9-#13). All Tiers 1-3 complete.\n   917→- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade\n   918→- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n   919→\n   920→---\n   921→\n   922→## 2026-03-20 — Run 38\n   923→\n   924→### What was done\n   925→\n   926→**pezantTools — Tailwind CSS 3→4 migration (PRs #56-#57, auto-merged)**\n   927→- Replaced `tailwindcss` v3.4 with `@tailwindcss/cli` v4.2.2\n   928→- Migrated theme config from `tailwind.config.js` to CSS `@theme` block (custom colors: ink, sand, ember, moss, sky; fonts: Fraunces, IBM Plex Sans; shadow-card)\n   929→- Replaced `@tailwind base/components/utilities` directives with `@import \"tailwindcss\"`"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fd6ea26a-cb05-47a5-8060-bb9857e501ca","uuid":"9af33438-07de-4883-98b8-16a4cb063345","timestamp":"2026-03-20T12:31:11.496Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"REDACTED_REPOS_ROOT/autonomousDev/logs/progress.md","content":"- **trustedCircle**: Feed page done (Tier 3 #11). Remaining Tier 3: share links (#12), sort & pagination (#13)\n- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 36\n\n### What was done\n\n**trustedCircle — Sort & pagination (Tier 3 #13) (PR #37-#39, auto-merged)**\n- Server-side sort support on 3 API endpoints:\n  - `GET /api/reviewers?sort=name|reviews|newest` — sort people by name (default), review count, or newest\n  - `GET /api/categories/:slug/reviews?sort=newest|rating_high|rating_low&page=N` — sort + offset pagination (20/page)\n  - `GET /api/reviewers/:handle?sort=newest|rating_high|rating_low` — sort reviewer's reviews\n- Reusable `SortPills` component for pill-style sort UI (ink/sand active state)\n- PeoplePage: sort pills (Name A–Z, Most reviews, Newest) alongside search filter\n- CategoryPage: sort pills in \"All reviews\" section + prev/next page navigation\n- PersonPage: sort pills below category filter for review ordering\n- 10 new tests: 3 for reviewer sort, 4 for category review sort + pagination, 3 for reviewer profile sort\n- 124 total tests (was 114), all passing, TypeScript clean, build verified\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: Sort & pagination done (Tier 3 #13). Remaining Tier 3: share links (#12)\n- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 37\n\n### What was done\n\n**trustedCircle — Share links (Tier 3 #12) (PR #41, auto-merged)**\n- `ShareButton` component with clipboard copy + Web Share API (native share sheet on mobile), pill-shaped design with \"Copied!\" feedback\n- Share button added to 4 pages: ReviewDetailPage, PersonPage, CategoryPage, ComparePage\n- Server-side OG meta tags middleware (`og-tags.ts`):\n  - Detects social media bot user-agents (Facebook, Twitter, Discord, Slack, LinkedIn, Telegram, WhatsApp, Google, Bing)\n  - Serves dynamic `og:title`, `og:description`, `og:image`, `og:url`, and Twitter Card meta tags\n  - Supports 4 entity types: reviews, reviewer profiles, categories, comparisons\n  - Handles base path stripping for production deployment\n  - Fallback default OG tags for unknown/home paths\n- 12 new tests: 8 for `getOgMeta` (all entity types, unknown entities, base path stripping, unmatched paths) + 4 for `renderOgHtml` (tag rendering, image inclusion/omission, HTML entity escaping)\n- 136 total tests (was 124), all passing, TypeScript clean, build verified\n\n### Survey findings (for future sessions)\n- **trustedCircle**: All Tier 3 features now complete (#9-#13). All Tiers 1-3 complete.\n- **pezantTools**: Only tailwindcss 3→4 remains as a pending major dep upgrade\n- **All repos**: Clean audit (except known unfixable transitive deps), tests passing, CI active, branches clean\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-20 — Run 38\n\n### What was done\n\n**pezantTools — Tailwind CSS 3→4 migration (PRs #56-#57, auto-merged)**\n- Replaced `tailwindcss` v3.4 with `@tailwindcss/cli` v4.2.2\n- Migrated theme config from `tailwind.config.js` to CSS `@theme` block (custom colors: ink, sand, ember, moss, sky; fonts: Fraunces, IBM Plex Sans; shadow-card)\n- Replaced `@tailwind base/components/utilities` directives with `@import \"tailwindcss\"`","numLines":60,"startLine":870,"totalLines":1055}}}
